MOTION DOCKET

93-332. Morgan v. Mattes.

In Mandamus. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of mandamus. Upon consideration of relator’s motion to expedite and “stay preceding [sic]” of trial date,

IT IS ORDERED by the court, that motion to expedite and “stay preceding [sic ]” of trial date be, and the same is hereby, denied, effective February 22, 1993.
